From: MLIR Python bindings utils
Subject: [PATCH 0006] Add mlir.utils: CFG visualization using Python IR API

Adds mlir/python/mlir/utils.py providing show_cfg() and get_function_cfg()
for MLIR function CFG visualization in Jupyter notebooks.  Uses
block.successors from the MLIR Python IR API for control-flow edges
(analogous to llvmlite's get_function_cfg / view_dot_graph pair).  On
Emscripten/JupyterLite renders via @hpcc-js/wasm CDN; on native Python
uses the graphviz subprocess.

